						<summary>

						<p>On the tiers, northern side of the base of <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine of the Perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 11: 982 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record an undertaking given by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Kīramaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Kalār-kkūṟṟam in Maḻa-nāḍu to Brahmādhirājaṉ Āchchiyaṉ Bhaṭṭaṉ Chakrapāṇi (probably a military official) to exempt the land, endowed by him for the bathing and attendant services to the God in the Rājakēsari-vishṇugriham on every <hi rend="italic">dvādasi</hi> day in the month of Mārgaḻi (see No. 96) from taxes <hi rend="italic">iṟai, veṭṭi, vēdiṉai, echchōṟu, ūriḍu-vari</hi> and other such <hi rend="italic">in lieu</hi> of some gold received from him by them.</p>						

						</summary>
